nd (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret of Balwearie was born in 1222, in Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland as the daughter of Sir Richard de Balweary. She married Sir Michael Scott 1st of Balwearie in 1242, in Dumfries and Galloway, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1292, in Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 70, and was buried in Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland."},"et":{"1222–1292":"1222–1292","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1217–1294":"1217–1294","1243–Male":"1243–Surnud","1249–1304":"1249–1304","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1217":"1217","1190":"1190","1249":"1249","1304":"1304","1222":"1222","1243":"1243","1242":"1242","1294":"1294","1292":"1292","1160":"1160","Balwearie Castle, Kirkcaldy, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland","Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland":"Kirkcaldy, Fife, Scotland","Murthokston, Dumfries and Galloway, Scotland":"Dumfries and Galloway, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1222–1292":"1222–1292","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1217–1294":"1217–1294","1243–Male":"1243–Kuollut","1249–1304":"1249–1304","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1217":"1217","1190":"1190","1249":"1249","1304":"1304","1222":"1222","1243":"1243","1242":"1242